Subject: [PATCH 7/7] ggml-cuda: warp-shfl butterfly fast path for TurboQuant fattn V dequant

Target: PrismML-Eng/llama.cpp tag prism-b9596-9fcaed7, after patches 0001-0006.

Implements the patch-0006 TODO: a warp-cooperative shfl-butterfly fast path in
fattn-common.cuh dequantize_V_tq (clean-room, like the rest of the CUDA
patchset — no code from the unlicensed community gist).

The vec kernel assigns the 8 four-code groups of one 32-value TurboQuant block
to 8 consecutive lanes (i0 % 32 == (lane % 8) * 4). The fast path exploits
that: each lane unpacks only its own 4 codes, then the 5-stage inverse
Walsh-Hadamard butterfly runs as 2 in-register stages (j bits 0-1) plus 3
__shfl_xor_sync stages across the aligned 8-lane group (j bits 2-4) — 16 adds
+ 12 shuffles per 4 outputs instead of the closed form's full-block decode +
4x32 parity-sum adds.

Safety: the lane-assignment assumption is verified warp-wide at runtime with
__all_sync, so the branch is warp-uniform by construction — any caller with a
different thread mapping (and the ne == 2 instantiation) degrades to the
closed-form reference path instead of hitting shuffle UB. HIP keeps the
reference path (wave64 + different vote semantics; TODO(v1.1) if ROCm support
lands). Both paths compute the same butterfly in the same pairwise order, so
numerics match the CPU reference within fp32 round-off; validated on-device
by vendor/tools/tq_cuda_numeric.cpp (run_kernel_tests.py stage 7) and by
llama-bench before/after tables in suiban/docs/benchmarks.md.
---
diff --git a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn-common.cuh b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn-common.cuh
index 2fbe638..79c25ee 100644
--- a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn-common.cuh
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn-common.cuh
@@ -621,39 +621,108 @@ static __device__ __forceinline__ void dequantize_V_q8_0(const void * __restrict
 // TurboQuant TQ3_0/TQ4_0 V cache (see turboquant.cuh). Unlike the per-element
 // formats above, TurboQuant dequantization needs the whole 32-value block (the
 // inverse randomized Hadamard transform mixes every coordinate into every
-// output), so each thread decodes the full block it lands in and evaluates its
-// ne outputs via the closed-form parity sum. The vec kernel always calls with
-// ne == 4 and i0 % 4 == 0, so a group never straddles a block boundary
-// (4 | 32). Reference implementation, correctness first.
-// TODO(v1.1): warp-cooperative shfl-butterfly fast path (the vec kernel's 32
-// V-threads of a warp read consecutive i0 of the same row) if profiling of the
-// decode-bound long-context case shows it matters.
+// output). Two paths compute the same values:
+//
+// * Warp-shfl fast path (CUDA, ne == 4): the vec kernel hands the 8 four-code
+//   groups of one 32-value block to 8 consecutive lanes (i0 % 32 ==
+//   (lane % 8) * 4 on every lane — verified warp-wide at runtime with
+//   __all_sync, so an unforeseen caller degrades to the reference path
+//   instead of hitting shuffle UB). Each lane loads only its own 4 codes; the
+//   5-stage inverse Walsh-Hadamard butterfly runs as 2 register stages
+//   (j bits 0-1, in-lane) plus 3 __shfl_xor_sync stages (j bits 2-4, across
+//   the aligned 8-lane group): 16 adds + 12 shuffles per 4 outputs instead of
+//   the closed form's full-block decode + 4x32 parity adds.
+// * Reference path (ne == 2, HIP, unexpected lane patterns): each thread
+//   decodes the full block it lands in and evaluates its ne outputs via the
+//   closed-form parity sum (validated by vendor/run_kernel_tests.py stage 6).
 template <typename T, int ne, ggml_type type_V>
 static __device__ __forceinline__ void dequantize_V_tq(const void * __restrict__ vx, void * __restrict__ dst, const int64_t i0) {
     static_assert(ne == 2 || ne == 4, "bad ne");
 
-    float c[QK_TQ];
-    float d;
-    if constexpr (type_V == GGML_TYPE_TQ3_0) {
-        const block_tq3_0 * x = (const block_tq3_0 *) vx;
-        const int64_t ib = i0 / QK_TQ3_0;
-        ggml_cuda_tq3_0_block_centroids(&x[ib], c);
-        d = __half2float(x[ib].d);
-    } else {
-        static_assert(type_V == GGML_TYPE_TQ3_0 || type_V == GGML_TYPE_TQ4_0, "bad type");
-        const block_tq4_0 * x = (const block_tq4_0 *) vx;
-        const int64_t ib = i0 / QK_TQ4_0;
-        ggml_cuda_tq4_0_block_centroids(&x[ib], c);
-        d = __half2float(x[ib].d);
-    }
-
     const int   j0 = i0 % QK_TQ;
-    const float dn = d * TQ_RSQRT32;
